about.summary: Beta regression for modeling beta-distributed dependent variables, e.g., rates and proportions. In addition to maximum likelihood regression (for both mean and precision of a beta-distributed response), bias-corrected and bias-reduced estimation as well as finite mixture models and recursive partitioning for beta regressions are provided.

name: r-betareg
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.1-3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-betareg
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/betareg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/betareg/betareg_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: cc19387ec516492d11cf59cdfa07e1733950a2af8196c1e155bc95939bc76246

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-formula
    - r-flexmix
    - r-lmtest
    - r-modeltools
    - r-sandwich
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-formula
    - r-flexmix
    - r-lmtest
    - r-modeltools
    - r-sandwich

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('betareg')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('betareg')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=betareg
  license: GPL-2 | GPL-3
  summary: Beta regression for modeling beta-distributed dependent variables, e.g., rates and
    proportions. In addition to maximum likelihood regression (for both mean and precision
    of a beta-distributed response), bias-corrected and bias-reduced estimation as well
    as finite mixture models and recursive partitioning for beta regressions are provided.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - sebastian-luna-valero
